file_summary: This CSS file provides comprehensive styling for a navigation bar, typically used in a web application's header. It defines the visual appearance of the `.navbar` element, setting its background color, borders, and spacing. A prominent feature is the custom styling for the brand logo (`.navbar a.navbar-brand`), which utilizes background images to display a logo with a subtle hover effect, likely related to "Spring Data Flow" branding. Navigation links (`.navbar li > a`) are styled with a specific sans-serif font, uppercase text, generous padding, and a clear hover state that changes their background and text color. The file also includes styles for the responsive navigation toggle button (`.navbar-toggle`), specifying the dimensions and spacing for its iconic bars. The overall design emphasizes a clean, corporate look with a dark background and a distinct green accent color, enhancing the user interface's navigation experience.
